headline: Got $1,000? Super Micro Computer Stock Is a Brilliant Backdoor AI Play
summary: Supermicro faces some headwinds due to tariffs.  Hardware companies like Nvidia (NASDAQ: NVDA) are powering the training of AI models, suppliers like Taiwan Semiconductor (NYSE: TSM) are building the chips for Nvidia, and software companies like Palantir (NASDAQ: PLTR) are providing platforms to deploy AI for real-world use.  While Nvidia is an excellent choice in this realm, so is Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ: SMCI).
